---
import ComingSoonRoomLayout from '../layouts/ComingSoonRoomLayout.astro';
---
<ComingSoonRoomLayout
  room="reference-desk"
  title="Reference Desk"
  subtitle="Ask the Librarian. She has read every room."
  sourceId="coming-soon-reference-desk"
>
  <p>
    The Reference Desk will host the Library's first
    artificial-intelligence Librarian — an always-available agent that has
    read every state dossier, every book in the Reading Room, every court
    opinion the Library holds, every primary source in its archives, and
    every chapter of <em>The Eighth Anchor</em> and
    <em>Schools of the Republic</em>. Ask her a question about America's
    school trust lands and she will answer with citations to the Library's
    own sources, in plain language, around the clock.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Why this room matters.</strong> The Library was built in
    cognitive partnership with frontier AI — two retired scholars reaching
    across all fifty states in three weeks because the cognitive technology
    of 2025 and 2026 finally let us do work that biological memory couldn't
    hold. The Reference Desk extends that partnership to the reader. A
    citizen who wants to know what her state's school trust earned last
    year, what the 1894 Enabling Act required, how
    <em>Meinhard v. Salmon</em> applies to a modern fund manager, or what
    the Land Ordinance of 1785 actually says — she should be able to ask,
    and get a real answer, without waiting for office hours.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>What the Librarian will and won't do.</strong> She will answer
    factual questions from the Library's content, cite her sources, and
    tell you when she doesn't know. She won't give legal advice, won't
    speculate beyond what the Library holds, won't take positions on active
    litigation, and won't pretend to be a person. The disclaimer at the top
    of every conversation will say so.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Manual fallback.</strong> Until the Librarian opens, a short
    form will let any visitor send a question that a human will read and
    answer. Public-interest questions and their answers will be posted
    here, with the asker's permission, so the next reader who is stuck
    doesn't have to start over.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Being planned.</strong> Target opening: early June 2026. The
    work runs on five tracks — indexing the Library's contents for
    retrieval, building the question-and-answer endpoint, designing the
    conversation interface to match the Library's visual identity,
    drafting the Librarian's character and guardrails, and stress-testing
    her against real questions before she opens to the public. The manual
    form will go up first.
  </p>
</ComingSoonRoomLayout>
